  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ht-mc-clm-ad-lb-6mo-001",
    "name": "HT-MC-BTC-CLM-AllocDrift-LiqBuffer-6m0",
    "description": "ACTUS Hybrid Treasury: BTC as CLM (Call Money) Contract\n\nMigration from STK/COM to CLM for the BTC position. CLM models BTC\ndeployed to a yield-producing lending platform (3% APY) with 7-day\ncallable notice. This avoids the feeRate NPE (Fix 1/2) and the\ninitialExchangeDate NPE (Fix 3) that plagued STK and COM.\n\nKey difference: CLM is a full debt instrument in ACTUS. Its parser\nmaps feeRate (defaults 0.0), notionalPrincipal, nominalInterestRate,\ndayCountConvention, and initialExchangeDate — all fields that STK/COM\nlacked, causing NPEs in STF_PP_rf2 and risksrv3 ContractModel.parse().\n\nNO CHANGES to actus-service (port 8083) or webapp needed.\nONLY risksrv3 behavioral models + this simulation JSON.\n\nPortfolio:\n  Contract 1: CLM  — 40 BTC ($2M @ $50K) lent at 3% APY, 7-day notice\n  Contract 2: PAM  — T-Bill #1 $500K zero-coupon, matures Mar 31\n  Contract 3: PAM  — T-Bill #2 $500K zero-coupon, matures May 31\n  Contract 4: PAM  — T-Bill #3 $250K zero-coupon, matures Jun 30\n  Contract 5: PAM  — T-Bill #4 $500K zero-coupon, matures Jul 31\n\nAllocationDriftModel updated with positionQuantity=40 and\ninitialNotionalPrincipal=2000000 for CLM mode quantity tracking.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
